---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
  title: "Release Notes Automation",
  client: "DevOps & Product",
  tags: ["Automation", "DevOps", "Docs", "CI/CD"],
  outcomes: [
    "Automated release notes generation from tags and commits",
    "Eliminated manual document creation time (2â€“4 hours per release)",
    "Provided consistent formatting across all teams",
    "Enabled release auditors to trace changes instantly"
  ],
  summary:
    "Automated release notes generation using structured templates, tagging, and CI/CD pipeline triggers."
};
---

<Base title={meta.title}>
  <main class="case-page max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-10 space-y-10">

    <!-- HEADER -->
    <header class="space-y-6 border-b border-slate-700/40 pb-8">
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-slate-400">
        Case Study Â· {meta.client}
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-white">
        {meta.title}
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg text-slate-200 leading-relaxed">
        {meta.summary}
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        {meta.tags.map((tag) => (
          <span class="rounded-full border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/60 px-3 py-1 text-xs text-slate-200">
            {tag}
          </span>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 mt-4">
        {meta.outcomes.map((o) => (
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-4 text-sm shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-slate-200">{o}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Overview</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-200 leading-relaxed">
        I built an automated <strong>Release Notes generation system</strong> that transformed
        commit data, PR metadata, and tags into standardized documentation. This removed manual
        work, reduced release delays, and guaranteed audit-friendly documentation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- PROBLEM -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Problem</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-200">Before automation, release notes were:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-200 space-y-1">
        <li>Written manually by developers</li>
        <li>Missing key information</li>
        <li>Inconsistently formatted</li>
        <li>Time consuming (hours per release)</li>
        <li>Frequently delivered late</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-slate-200 mt-2">This created gaps for:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-200 space-y-1">
        <li>Product managers</li>
        <li>QA</li>
        <li>Release partners</li>
        <li>SOC 2 auditors</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- APPROACH -->
    <section class="space-y-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Approach</h2>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-white text-lg">ðŸ”¹ 1. Defined a Standard Release Notes Template</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-200 leading-relaxed">
          Included sections for:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-slate-200 list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
          <li>Summary of changes</li>
          <li>Breaking changes</li>
          <li>API changes</li>
          <li>Dependency updates</li>
          <li>Bug fixes</li>
          <li>Testing validation</li>
          <li>Links to PRs and commits</li>
          <li>Rollback instructions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-white text-lg">ðŸ”¹ 2. Implemented Commit Tagging Conventions</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-200">Examples:</p>
        <ul class="text-slate-200 list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
          <li>feat: new tax calculation</li>
          <li>fix: payment double-charge bug</li>
          <li>docs: updated API reference</li>
          <li>refactor: improved entity service</li>
          <li>chore: CI pipeline cleanup</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-white text-lg">ðŸ”¹ 3. Created a CI/CD Workflow</h3>
        <ul class="text-slate-200 list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
          <li>Detects tags or new release</li>
          <li>Parses commits via <code>git log</code> or GitHub API</li>
          <li>Groups changes by category</li>
          <li>Builds formatted Markdown/PDF output</li>
          <li>Uploads as release asset</li>
          <li>Posts summary to Slack / Teams</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-slate-200 mt-2">Developers only tag the release â€” documentation is generated automatically.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-white text-lg">ðŸ”¹ 4. Added Cross-Team Validation</h3>
        <ul class="text-slate-200 list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
          <li>QA validation results</li>
          <li>Security validation status</li>
          <li>Related tickets (ClickUp, Jira)</li>
          <li>Migration notes for developers</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- OUTCOMES -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Outcomes</h2>
      <ul class="text-slate-200 list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
        <li>âœ” 0 manual hours spent writing notes</li>
        <li>âœ” 100% consistent formatting across releases</li>
        <li>âœ” Full change traceability for auditors</li>
        <li>âœ” Faster release cycle & fewer delays</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- EXAMPLE ASSETS -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Example Assets</h2>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">

        <!-- Card 1 -->
        <a
          href="/templates/release-notes-template.md"
          class="asset-card group flex items-start justify-between rounded-xl border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/60 p-4 text-sm shadow-sm hover:border-slate-500 hover:bg-slate-800 transition"
        >
          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="font-semibold text-white">Release Notes Template (MD)</p>
            <p class="text-slate-300">Standardized template used for commit-driven documentation.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-slate-400">â¬‡</span>
        </a>

        <!-- Card 2 -->
        <a
          href="/templates/release-workflow.yaml"
          class="asset-card group flex items-start justify-between rounded-xl border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/60 p-4 text-sm shadow-sm hover:border-slate-500 hover:bg-slate-800 transition"
        >
          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="font-semibold text-white">GitHub Actions Workflow (YAML)</p>
            <p class="text-slate-300">CI workflow that builds and publishes automated notes.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-slate-400">â¬‡</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <!-- LOCAL PAGE-ONLY STYLES -->
  <style>
    /* Bright text for this case page only */
    .case-page p,
    .case-page li {
      color: #f8fafc;
    }

    .case-page h1,
    .case-page h2,
    .case-page h3,
    .case-page h4 {
      color: #ffffff;
    }

    /* Asset cards (dark mode) */
    .asset-card,
    .asset-card * {
      color: #ffffff;
    }
  </style>

</Base>
